title: MCAT Variety Pack
description:
Notes: AAMC practice test #4 questions and answers are not in the right order, though the answers are there if you look for them.  The other tests have the answers in the correct order but many are off by 2 questions as the essays are not included (i.e. answer #112 may correspond to question #114).


Personal recommendation: The Berkeley Review books for chem and physics are the most comprehensive and I would TBR primarily for those subjects.  The EK biology book is excellent and was in my opinion the most efficient way to study for the biology section.


The MCAT practice tests are only useful the first run through each one, so make sure you're ready to start writing tests before you use them!


Good luck!
